---
---

<section class="spaced" id="how" style="background: var(--surface-2); border-top: 1px solid var(--border); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-head">
      <span class="eyebrow"><span class="blue-dot"></span>How it works</span>
      <h2><span class="primary-blue">Three steps.</span> <span class="accent">No setup, no software</span></h2>
      <p>You don't install anything. You don't configure DNS. You pick a name, give it to your vendors, and the inbox starts working.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="op-flow">
      <div class="op-flow-step">
        <div class="op-flow-num">[01]</div>
        <div class="op-flow-title">Pick your inbox name</div>
        <p class="op-flow-desc">Choose a short handle — for example <span class="mono">silva@invoicepass.app</span>. It's yours, it's permanent, it's free.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="op-flow-step">
        <div class="op-flow-num">[02]</div>
        <div class="op-flow-title">Send invoices to it</div>
        <p class="op-flow-desc">Give the address to vendors. Or forward existing invoices from Gmail, Outlook, anywhere. PDFs are parsed automatically.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="op-flow-step">
        <div class="op-flow-num">[03]</div>
        <div class="op-flow-title">Review them in your portal</div>
        <p class="op-flow-desc">Every invoice is signed, deduped, and organized by vendor. Export to your accountant when you're ready.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
